<tree expanded="true" show-heading="true" show-metadata="true" toc="false" root="false"><frontmatter> <anchor>7842</anchor> <rss>jms-000C.rss.xml</rss> <taxon>Remark</taxon> <addr>jms-000C</addr>  <route>jms-000C.xml</route> <date><year>2023</year> <month>1</month> <day>18</day></date> <authors><author><link href="jonmsterling.xml" type="local" jonmsterling="addr">Jon Sterling</link></author> </authors> <title>Kernels as equalizers</title> </frontmatter> <mainmatter><p>Evidently, the <link href="jms-0009.xml" type="local" addr="jms-0009" title="Kernel">kernel</link> of a morphism <tex>A \xrightarrow {f} B</tex> in a <link href="jms-000B.xml" type="local" addr="jms-000B" title="Category with zero morphisms">category with zero morphisms</link> is the <em>equalizer</em> of  <tex>A \xrightarrow {f} B</tex> with the zero morphism <tex>A \xrightarrow {0} B</tex>.</p></mainmatter> <backmatter><contributions/> <context/> <related><tree expanded="false" show-heading="true" show-metadata="true" toc="false" root="false"><frontmatter> <anchor>7843</anchor> <rss>jms-000B.rss.xml</rss> <taxon>Definition</taxon> <addr>jms-000B</addr>  <route>jms-000B.xml</route> <date><year>2023</year> <month>1</month> <day>18</day></date> <authors><author><link href="jonmsterling.xml" type="local" jonmsterling="addr">Jon Sterling</link></author> </authors> <title>Category with zero morphisms</title> </frontmatter> <mainmatter><p>A <em>category with zero morphisms</em> is defined to be a category <link href="jms-000H.xml" type="local" addr="jms-000H" title="Enriched category">enriched</link> in the category of pointed sets and strict maps. The distinguished point of <tex>\mathbf {hom} _{ \mathcal {A} } { \mathopen {} \left ( A , B \right ) \mathclose {}}</tex> shall be written <tex>0</tex>.</p></mainmatter> </tree><tree expanded="false" show-heading="true" show-metadata="true" toc="false" root="false"><frontmatter> <anchor>7844</anchor> <rss>jms-0009.rss.xml</rss> <taxon>Definition</taxon> <addr>jms-0009</addr>  <route>jms-0009.xml</route> <date><year>2023</year> <month>1</month> <day>18</day></date> <authors><author><link href="jonmsterling.xml" type="local" jonmsterling="addr">Jon Sterling</link></author> </authors> <title>Kernel</title> </frontmatter> <mainmatter><p>Let <tex>\mathcal {A}</tex> be a <link href="jms-000B.xml" type="local" addr="jms-000B" title="Category with zero morphisms">category with zero morphisms</link>. Then the <em>kernel</em> of a morphism <tex>A \xrightarrow {f} B</tex> in <tex>\mathcal {A}</tex> is defined to be a morphism <tex>K \xrightarrow {k}{A}</tex> such that for any <tex>X \xrightarrow {h}A</tex> with <tex>h;f=0</tex>, there exists a unique map <tex>X \xrightarrow {}K</tex>
factoring <tex>X \xrightarrow {h}A</tex> through <tex>K \xrightarrow {k}{A}</tex> in the sense of the diagram below:</p>
  
